Citations
Date:  0/0/1975
Source:  Battles, Buggies and Babies
Author:  JOHNSTONE-SMITH
Vol / Page:  41
Edition:
Quote:  Bailers are dogs which can bail up a wild pig. Certain dogs being good at finding and having 'found' would give the signal when the bailers would join in, so confusing and worrying the pig that it would stand at bay.
